{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Last Tango in Halifax'' episodes}}
[[File:Derek Jacobi.jpg|thumb|200px|right|upright|Derek Jacobi, who plays the male romantic lead in ''Last Tango In Halifax''.]]
'''''[[Last Tango in Halifax]]''''' is a [[Television in the United Kingdom|British]] romantic [[drama]] series that started airing on [[BBC One]] on 20 November 2012. To date twelve episodes have aired.  The series was written by screenwriter [[Sally Wainwright]], loosely adapting the story of her mother's second marriage.<ref name=WainwrightPR>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/mediapacks/tango/writer.html|title=Interview with writer, Sally Wainwright|work=BBC Press Office|publisher=[[BBC Online]]|date=13 August 2012|accessdate=17 April 2013}}</ref> ''Last Tango in Halifax'' stars [[Derek Jacobi]] and [[Anne Reid]] as former childhood sweethearts Alan and Celia who are now in their seventies. The series follows their romance following a reunion via social media, sixty years after their last meeting. The lives of Celia's daughter Caroline ([[Sarah Lancashire]]) and Alan's daughter Gillian ([[Nicola Walker]]) often provide a source of drama and are used to explore wider themes surrounding family.<ref name=WainwrightDM>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2229865/Screenwriter-Sally-Wainwright-Can-fall-love-75.html|title=Can you fall in love at 75? Screenwriter Sally Wainwright on how her mother's sweet late-life romance inspired her new drama|last=Wainwright|first=Sally|work=[[Daily Mail]]|publisher=[[Associated Newspapers]]|date=9 November 2012|accessdate=17 April 2013}}</ref><ref name=WainwrightPR/>

The first series of ''Last Tango In Halifax'' aired between 20 November and 19 December 2012. It the UK's highest rated new mid-week television drama of 2012 and was re-commissioned for a second series.<ref name=series2>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/bbc-one-drama-last-tango-in-halifax-recommissioned-for-second-series-8406268.html|title=BBC One drama Last Tango in Halifax re-commissioned for second series|last=Wyatt|first=Daisy|accessdate=18 April 2013|date=11 December 2012|work=[[The Independent]]|publisher=Independent Print Limited}}</ref> The second series aired from 19 November 2013 to 24 December 2014. The series was re-commissioned for a third series on 24 December 2013, ahead of the final episode of the second series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2013/last-tango-series3|title=BBC One commissions third series of Last Tango In Halifax|work=BBC Media Centre|date=24 December 2013|accessdate=5 November 2014}}</ref>

