 |ShortSummary= Recently widowed Celia Dawson ([[Anne Reid]]) contacts Alan Buttershaw ([[Derek Jacobi]])&nbsp;<U+2014> a former romantic interest whom she has not seen in 60 years&nbsp;<U+2014> on the social networking site [[Facebook]]. Celia's daughter Caroline ([[Sarah Lancashire]]) is surprised by the revelation, though distracted by her own romantic problems involving her adulterous husband ([[Tony Gardner]]) and her own affair with a female colleague, Kate ([[Nina Sosanya]]). Alan and Celia meet in [[Skipton]] and immediately rekindle their friendship. Celia's car is later damaged in pursuit of a young man who stole Alan's vehicle. Caroline and Alan's daughter Gillian ([[Nicola Walker]]) clash on first encounter after rushing to collect their parents; both are shocked to discover that Alan and Celia plan to marry.
