 |ShortSummary= Three months after the previous episode, William leaves for university, and Lawrence tells his mother he wants to live with his dad, who is now co-habituating with a pregnant Judith. Gillian is jealous of Robbie's new partner, Cheryl. Kate reveals she is twelve weeks pregnant; though Caroline is restrained in her presence, she is later overcome with emotion. Gillian volunteers her and Caroline's services to plan Alan and Celia's second wedding. Alan and Celia visit Celia's estranged sister Muriel, whom Celia fell out with when Muriel married Celia's love interest. After a day out together researching the wedding, a drunken Gillian tells Caroline she deliberately killed her husband and staged his suicide, as she could take no more of his abuse and feared he'd one day kill her.
